Financial information, such as bank account number, credit or debit card number, and other financial information.
Commercial information, such as purchase history and engagement with the Services.
Information from third parties, such as personal information stored with third parties that you choose to provide to us. By linking your third-party accounts, you authorize Johto to have access to this information and you agree that Johto may collect and use this information in accordance with our Privacy Policy.
Internet, device and browsing activity, such as browser type and settings, device type and settings, operating system, mobile network information including carrier name and phone number, and application version number.
Usage data, such as the interaction of your apps, browsers, and devices with our services, including IP address, crash reports, system activity, and the date, time, and referrer URL of your request.
Message content, including messages you send or receive within an organization or that you send to Breakroom or Breakroom Support.
User-generated content, including files you upload through the service such as images, video, and audio.
Personal Information of your Employees that You Invite to Use the Crew Platform. Information of Employees you provide to Breakroom, including their name, phone number, IP address, and limited location information for the sole purpose of providing Location-Based Group functionality. We use this information to invite Employees to join Breakroom. ¬†An Important Note: ¬†You and your organization are responsible for, and must obtain, any and all consents required by law (including, without limitation, verifiable consent, where applicable) from Employees before providing any Employee personal information to Breakroom.
Device Information. ¬†Log data, including your mobile device, screen resolution, and load time when using the mobile Crew Platform, and operating system, browser type and version, and IP address when using our web Crew Platform. We use the IP address to understand your general location and log data to improve the Crew Platform functionality, performance, and user experience.
Information you provide to us when interacting with our customer support team or other team members via email, phone, live chat, or other correspondence.
Geolocation information, which we may obtain when using mobile versions of our Services, which helps us offer features such as time clock usage, or alerts for scheduled shifts or breaks, or other jobs that might be nearby and of interest to you.
Inferences, including information about your interests and preferences.
When you interact with Johto through the Site and Services, we receive and store certain personally non-identifiable information. Such information, which is collected passively using various technologies, cannot presently be used to specifically identify you. Johto may store such information itself or such information may be included in databases owned and maintained by Johto affiliates, agents or service providers. The Services may use such information and pool it with other information to track, for example, the total number of visitors to our Site, the number of visitors to each page of our Site, and the domain names of our visitors' Internet service providers. It is important to note that no personal information is available or used in this process.
